The paper focuses on adversarial attacks on neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the possibility of attacks by a skillful adversary, which falls under the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses image datasets and modifies the data by changing just one pixel, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of attacks on publicly available datasets, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
